US: Repetition is the mother of wisdom
It is comical that Barack Obama, the president with the reputation of the smartest man, as a diligent student repeats in the Afghan question the strategy of his predecessor, to which he himself took for the fooliest.
When he finally revealed his Afghan approach, expected with anxiety, it was demonstrated that it is a copy of the script used for Iraq by Bush, created three years ago.
Not only in the same text is the "equal" speech used several times in Iraq, but it did not hesitate to use the title of the Bush statement of January 2007 for its own statement: "A new way forward".
It was himself, who three years ago criticized Bush's idea of sending new military reinforcements to Iraq, the country that is suffering from civil war, and that criticized him as "an irresponsible decision with catastrophic consequences."
The following months, however, showed that Bush's strategy, based on the recommendations of field captains, was the only possible and successful, so that there is no talk today about Iraq in the news.
Bush's reputation did not improve, however objectively left his successor a much more favourable initial situation than he could expect.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama expects the miracle to be repeated.
The camp captains asked him again to increase the military contingent, especially the commander-in-chief of the general Afghan operation Stanley McCristal. He, even in spite of the traditional subordinate relations, submitted to the undecided gunmen in the White House for a harsh criticism.
He asked 40,000 men to improve the situation.
The president hesitated for three months, but nothing better happened to him, so at least he tricked the general about 10,000 soldiers.
He managed to get Europe to promise him a further 5,000, although he himself had at least 10,000 before.
The most problematic thing in Obama's entire strategy seems to be his goal, starting to withdraw Afghanistan's troops in 18 months and finalize this procedure in three years.The whole Obama doctrine generated more questions than the answers he offered.
Many doubt that the increase bears the same fruit as the procedure in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars in recent years, Iraq's society is relatively well organized, its leaders respect the agreements.
The situation in Afghanistan is different: no one can be trusted and no agreement is reached.
Under these conditions it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces, if they are accustomed to changing the chief each day according to their needs.
Political institutions, although formally established, will remain only a people of Potemkin. After him will remain patriarchal tribal relations.
Balancing the interests of different ethnic groups is extraordinarily complicated due to confusing relations, even more complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Not even establishing a state that is "capable of action", a minimum objective of the entire operation, seems very real.
The horizon of Obama's strategy is shocking for his volunteerism.
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has continued to worsen and is now about to explode.
Only a romantic soul, who knows nothing about reality, can believe that the military sent to war to "come home soon," will do some miracle here.
From a political point of view, fixing the date of withdrawal of troops is purely irresponsible, as the Taliban will consider it an indirect declaration of US defeat.
The last NATO summit showed that Europeans are increasingly willing to participate in military operations in Afghanistan.
European politicians don't know, and they don't want to explain to their voters, what the security of Germany or Italy has to do with the war with Hindu Kush.
The other factor, capable of radically affecting the situation, is the development of events in Iran.
If the situation continues to worsen and increased sanctions do not have any effect on Iranians, the US will have to make a difficult decision: to try to solve the problem with military force or not.
It will be necessary to seek answers precisely when, according to Obama, America starts the triumphal withdrawal of Afghanistan's troops.
However, each solution in this way will mean a dramatic reversal for the Afghan situation.
The only positive point for Barack Obama is the fact that there are three years left for the presidential elections and that is why there is still a lot of time left to find another strategy, if this is a total failure.
